707475f-c.text:
(1)
Ave. Y., north side, between East 14th and 15th 8treets, showing the Emmans farmhouse known as "0ld Homestead'. Eugene L. Armbruster states thet from 1857-1860, it was ocoupied by one Emmons, and in 1872 by A.J. Emmons. However the Beer atlas of Long Island (1873) states the house be that of J. Emmer. In 1890 it was owned by an M. Teets. Since 1912 a Bessie Mill has occupied it. It is not in the atlas of
1929, evidently having been demolished.
March 1923.
Eugene L: Armbruster Collection.
(2)
The same, another view.
March 1923.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
(3)
The same, showing a side view.
March 1923.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
(4)
The same, showing the barnd.
March 1923.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
